OL,4,Cdamage 'sensitive habitat' for rare
OL,5,Cwildlife
OL,7,FLorraine Wall, from Friends of the
OL,8,FLake District, argues that while
OL,9,Feveryone should be able to enjoy the
OL,10,Fbeach, such a sharp increase in
OL,11,Fvisitors will cause long-lasting
OL,12,Fdamage.
OL,14,FShe said: "Of course people want to
OL,15,Fenjoy this wonderful area, and we
OL,16,Fwouldn't want to stop that from
OL,17,Fhappening but as with any sensitive
OL,18,Fhabitat it's about finding that
OL,19,Fbalance and this would tip that
OL,20,Fbalance."
